shapes:OfferTemplateShape
	a sh:NodeShape ;
	sh:targetClass ids:ContractOffer ;
	# message for violation of the sh:node constraint:
    sh:message "<https://raw.githubusercontent.com/International-Data-Spaces-Association/InformationModel/master/examples/contract-and-usage-policy/templates/OfferTemplateShape.ttl> (HasProviderOrConsumerNodeShape): In a _:ContractOffer a) the ids:provider property must point to one participant or b) the ids:consumer property must point to one participant  or c) the ids:provider and the ids:consumer must point to one participant. This can in any case be a) an IRI or b) an ids:Participant."@en ;
	sh:node shapes:HasProviderOrConsumerNodeShape ;
	sh:property shapes:OfferTemplate-atLeastOneOfferPermissionPropertyShape ;
.

shapes:HasProviderOrConsumerNodeShape
    a sh:NodeShape ;
    sh:or(
        [
            sh:property shapes:HasProviderOrConsumer-providerPropertyShape ;
        ] 
        [
            sh:property shapes:HasProviderOrConsumer-consumerPropertyShape ;
        ]
        [
            sh:property shapes:HasProviderOrConsumer-providerPropertyShape ;
            sh:property shapes:HasProviderOrConsumer-consumerPropertyShape ;
        ]
    ) ;
    sh:severity     sh:Violation ;
.

shapes:HasProviderOrConsumer-providerPropertyShape
    a sh:PropertyShape ;
    sh:path ids:provider ;
    sh:node shapes:ParticipantTemplateOptionsShape ;
    sh:minCount     1 ;
    sh:maxCount     1 ;
    sh:severity     sh:Violation ;
    sh:message "<https://raw.githubusercontent.com/International-Data-Spaces-Association/InformationModel/master/examples/contract-and-usage-policy/templates/OfferTemplate.ttl> (HasProviderOrConsumer-providerPropertyShape): In a _:ContractOffer or _:ContractRequest a) the ids:provider property must point to one participant or b) the ids:consumer property must point to one participant  or c) the ids:provider and the ids:consumer must point to one participant each. This can in any case be a) an IRI or b) an ids:Participant."@en ;
.

shapes:HasProviderOrConsumer-consumerPropertyShape
    a sh:PropertyShape ;
    sh:path ids:consumer ;
    sh:node shapes:ParticipantTemplateOptionsShape ;
    sh:minCount     1 ;
    sh:maxCount     1 ;
    sh:severity     sh:Violation ;
    sh:message "<https://raw.githubusercontent.com/International-Data-Spaces-Association/InformationModel/master/examples/contract-and-usage-policy/templates/OfferTemplate.ttl> (HasProviderOrConsumer-consumerPropertyShape): In a _:ContractOffer or _:ContractRequest a) the ids:provider property must point to one participant or b) the ids:consumer property must point to one participant  or c) the ids:provider and the ids:consumer must point to one participant each. This can in any case be a) an IRI or b) an ids:Participant."@en ;
.	


shapes:OfferTemplate-atLeastOneOfferPermissionPropertyShape
    a sh:PropertyShape ;
    sh:path			ids:permission ;
    sh:node	        shapes:OfferPermissionTemplateShape ;
    sh:minCount		1 ;
    sh:severity     sh:Violation ;
    sh:message      "<https://raw.githubusercontent.com/International-Data-Spaces-Association/InformationModel/master/examples/contract-and-usage-policy/templates/OfferTemplateShape.ttl> (OfferTemplate-atLeastOneOfferPermissionPropertyShape): In a _:ContractOffer the ids:permission property must point to at least one ids:Permission. In the ids:Permission, at least the ids:target and ids:action properties and one of (ids:assigner and ids:assignee) have to be specified."@en ;
.